You are only updating notes. Following are some descriptions and examples of different ways to use the note property in a description. Use these as a reference when updating note in the description.

## note
See the "description" model for all properties.

Note types must be from the "note" controlled list unless a different controlled list is specified in other instructions.

### Abstract

```json
{
  "note": [
    {
      "type": "abstract",
      "value": "This is an abstract of the resource."
    }
  ]
}
```

### Summary

```json
{
  "note": [
    {
      "type": "summary",
      "value": "This is a summary of the resource."
    }
  ]
}
```

### Table of contents

```json
{
  "note": [
    {
      "type": "table of contents",
      "value": "Chapter 1. Chapter 2."
    }
  ]
}
```

### Content warning

```json
{
  "note": [
    {
      "type": "content warning",
      "displayLabel": "Content advice",
      "value": "Content warning: contains racist and ableist content."
    }
  ]
}
```

### Formatted notes

#### Italics
Surround the text to be italicized with <i> and </i> (like the HTML italics tag).

```json
{
  "note": [
    {
      "type": "abstract",
      "value": "This is an <i>abstract</i> of the resource."
    }
  ]
}
```

#### Line breaks
Paragraph breaks may be inserted into a value with the <p> tag.
  
```json
{
  "note": [
    {
      "type": "abstract",
      "value": "This is an abstract of the resource.<p>This is the second paragraph of the abstract."
    }
  ]
}
```

